{
  "doc_id": "50533",
  "text": "More than one quarter of all genes that are mutated in HRD encode proteins that are responsible for cilium functions or development [CITATION_1] , highlighting the importance of this organelle for photoreceptor cell homeostasis and thus for vision in general. In this work, we demonstrate that FAM161A is a ciliary protein, interacts with other proteins involved in ciliopathies and plays a role in cilium assembly.",
